#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:1
msgid "Start Date: 2014-10-15"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:2
msgid ""
"RFC PR: [rust-lang/rfcs#356](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/356)"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:3
msgid ""
"Rust Issue: [rust-lang/rust#18073](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/"
"issues/18073)"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:5
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:7
msgid ""
"This is a conventions RFC that proposes that the items exported from a "
"module should _never_ be prefixed with that module name. For example, we "
"should have `io::Error`, not `io::IoError`."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:11
msgid ""
"(An alternative design is included that special-cases overlap with the "
"`prelude`.)"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:14
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:16
msgid ""
"Currently there is no clear prohibition around including the module's name "
"as a prefix on an exported item, and it is sometimes done for type names "
"that are feared to be \"popular\" (like `Error` and `Result` being `IoError` "
"and `IoResult`) for clarity."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:21
msgid ""
"This RFC include two designs: one that entirely rules out such prefixes, and "
"one that rules it out _except_ for names that overlap with the prelude. Pros/"
"cons are given for each."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:25
msgid "Detailed design"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:27
msgid ""
"The main rule being proposed is very simple: the items exported from a "
"module should never be prefixed with the module's name."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:30 src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:59
msgid "Rationale:"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:32
msgid "Avoids needless stuttering like `io::IoError`."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:33
msgid "Any ambiguity can be worked around:"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:34
msgid "Either qualify by the module, i.e. `io::Error`,"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:35
msgid "Or rename on import: `use io::Error as IoError`."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:36
msgid "The rule is extremely simple and clear."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:38 src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:64
msgid "Downsides:"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:40
msgid "The name may already exist in the module wanting to export it."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:41
msgid ""
"If that's due to explicit imports, those imports can be renamed or module-"
"qualified (see above)."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:43
msgid ""
"If that's due to a _prelude_ conflict, however, confusion may arise due to "
"the conventional _global_ meaning of identifiers defined in the prelude (i."
"e., programmers do not expect prelude imports to be shadowed)."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:47
msgid ""
"Overall, the RFC author believes that _if_ this convention is adopted, "
"confusion around redefining prelude names would gradually go away, because "
"(at least for things like `Result`) we would come to expect it."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:51
msgid "Alternative design"
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:53
msgid ""
"An alternative rule would be to never prefix an exported item with the "
"module's name, _except_ for names that are also defined in the prelude, "
"which _must_ be prefixed by the module's name."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:57
msgid "For example, we would have `io::Error` and `io::IoResult`."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:61
msgid "Largely the same as the above, but less decisively."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:62
msgid "Avoids confusion around prelude-defined names."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:66
msgid ""
"Retains stuttering for some important cases, e.g. custom `Result` types, "
"which are likely to be fairly common."
msgstr ""

#: src/0356-no-module-prefixes.md:68
msgid "Makes it even more problematic to expand the prelude in the future."
msgstr ""
